answers.q: what is error code e314 on edd
answers.a: E314 refers to gum guaiac (guaiacum), a plant-derived antioxidant food additive, and is unrelated to EDD error codes.
E314 is the food-additive code for gum guaiac, a natural antioxidant from Guaiacum trees; it has no connection to that website or content labels.
E314 (gum guaiac) is a purified resin from Guaiacum sanctum/officinale trees and does not have a sexâ€”it's an extracted plant material.

answers.q: guaiacum sanctum why type of flowers
answers.a: Guaiacum sanctum bears blue to purple flowers, but for E314 the relevant part is the resin from the wood, not the flowers.
Food-grade guaiacum (E314, gum guaiac) is obtained by collecting the natural resin from Guaiacum tree heartwood and refining it for use as an antioxidant in foods.
